  "notes_content": "<h2>Differential Abundance</h2><p>ANCOM-BC results per contrast. The default cutoff is q &lt; 0.05 (FDR-adjusted). The volcano shows effect size (log-fold change) vs significance; the DA-barplot ranks top taxa per contrast.</p><p>Use them together: a tile that's significant on the volcano but ranks low on the barplot has small effect size; a high-ranking barplot taxon that doesn't pass the volcano threshold is likely under-powered.</p>",
